thesis.description: This thesis discusses some of the Operations Research efforts in the health care field, the theory and implementation of simulation techniques, and a deatiled model of the Biochemistry Laboratory of teh Royal Victoria Hospital, Montreal. Particular attention is given to an arriva; generation technique in which the arrival rate varies and the arrivals themselves are batched. Validation and expermiental runs are discussed, the latter with an orientation towards the impact of the implications on Management. Numerous computer generated plots are included in the appendices. The model is sufficiently general to be applied to other hospital laboratories.
